<paragraph id="8E44F264FFF8FF98E6EEA368B065322A" blockId="11.[151,562,1555,1614]" box="[151,364,1590,1614]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
(
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFF8FF98E6E6A368B1FC322A" box="[159,245,1590,1614]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–40" captionStartId="59.[151,264,745,768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,724]" captionTargetId="figure-119@59.[151,1435,193,724]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURES 34–40. ♀. 34–38, areolet, fore wing, dorsal. 34, Debilos typurum sp. nov., Holotype. 35, D. prionilix sp. nov., Holotype. 36, D. trochanteratum (Szépligeti). Specimen from Brazil, RO, Candeias do Jamari, 28.I–4.II.2006 (UFES). 37, D. aserum sp. nov., Holotype. 38, D. anokum sp. nov., Holotype. 39, 40, fore wing, dorsal (areolet at right superior corner), arrow: crossvein 1cu-a; Holotypes. 39, D. tasamunum sp. nov. 40, D. owinum sp. nov. Illustrations not to scale." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs 37</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFF8FF98E778A368B024322A" box="[257,301,1590,1614]" captionStart="FIGURES 106–110" captionStartId="67.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[199,1388,193,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-70@67.[198,1388,193,1846]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURES 106–110. Holotypes, ♀, lateral. 106, Debilos okum sp. nov. 107, D. makirum sp. nov. 108, D. umentum sp. nov. 109, D. aserum sp. nov. 110, D. anokum sp. nov. Illustrations not to scale." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">109</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFF8FF98E740A368B06D322A" box="[313,356,1590,1614]" captionStart="FIGURES 142–147" captionStartId="74.[151,263,1521,1544]" captionTargetBox="[233,1354,193,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-78@74.[233,1354,193,1500]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="FIGURES 142–147. Diagrams with distribution records for: 142, Debilos anokum sp. nov.; 143, D. aserum sp. nov.; 144, D. makirum sp. nov.; 145, D. masipum sp. nov.; 146, D. okarum sp. nov.; 147, D. okum sp. nov." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">143</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFF8FF98E6EEA320B54D329B" blockId="11.[151,1436,1662,2036]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFF8FF98E6EEA320B02132F2" box="[151,296,1662,1687]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" reason="1">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFF8FF98E6EEA320B02832F3" bold="true" box="[151,289,1662,1687]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Female. Fore wing 
<quantity id="49035F81FFF8FF98E473A320B37832F2" box="[522,625,1662,1686]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.52" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="5.52">5.52 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFF8FF98E402A320B3B132F2" box="[635,696,1662,1686]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Head</emphasis>
: Antenna with 25 flagellomeres. Clypeus mostly smooth but with scarce punctures, slightly convex, regularly curved, CWH 1.95; MWC 0.67, MLW 2.00, MWW 0.50; malar space moderately long, MSM 1.00; supra-antennal area with faint, median, longitudinal carina; minimum distance from eye margin to occipital carina laterally approximately same width of mandible base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFF8FF9FE6BEA255B07D35A3" blockId="11.[151,1436,1662,2036]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1437,151,1713]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFF8FF98E6BEA255B0363346" box="[199,319,1803,1826]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFF8FF98E6BEA255B0363346" box="[199,319,1803,1826]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Mesosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFF8FF98E72FA254B0C83346" box="[342,449,1802,1826]" captionStart="FIGURES 106–110" captionStartId="67.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[199,1388,193,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-70@67.[198,1388,193,1846]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURES 106–110. Holotypes, ♀, lateral. 106, Debilos okum sp. nov. 107, D. makirum sp. nov. 108, D. umentum sp. nov. 109, D. aserum sp. nov. 110, D. anokum sp. nov. Illustrations not to scale." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 109</figureCitation>
). Pronotum lateral portion next to collar inconspicuously strigate-rugose, next to mesopleuron inconspicuously corrugated, epomia faint; notaulus faintly impressed, uniformly sculptured with mesoscutum, not reaching middle of mesoscutum; mesopleuron dorsal half medially faintly strigulate-rugulose, ventral half without distinct ridges or rugae, epicnemial carina restricted to ventral 0.8 of mesopleuron, posteriorly inconspicuously, sparsely corrugated; mesopleural groove moderately corrugated; sternaulus anterior half faintly corrugated; postpectal carina medially straight; metapleuron, subapical fovea shallow, subcircular; pleural carina stout; propodeum anterior area very long, PLL 1.30, anterior transverse carina distinct, complete, slightly, uniformly curved, posterior area faintly strigate-rugose, with faint ridges medially distinctly arched backwards, spiracle distinctly elliptic, SWL 1.80, propodeal apophyses long, thorn-shaped, AHD 2.15. Legs: Hind t4 posterior lobe about 0.33 × as long as anterior lobe. Fore wing vein (Rs+M)b perfectly straight, limit with crossvein 1m-cu distinct, ramellus absent; vein Rs&amp;1M uniformly slightly curved; crossvein 1cu-a uniformly to posteriorly slightly convex, arising distinctly apicad vein Rs&amp;1M, by about 0.2–0.3 × 1cu-a length, angle with vein M+Cu about 90 degrees; vein 2Cua moderately shorter than crossvein 2cu-a, FWC 0.64; areolet small, APH 0.63; vein 2Ma distinctly shorter than vein 2Mb (
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFFFFF9FE477A437B36835E5" box="[526,609,361,385]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–40" captionStartId="59.[151,264,745,768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,724]" captionTargetId="figure-119@59.[151,1435,193,724]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURES 34–40. ♀. 34–38, areolet, fore wing, dorsal. 34, Debilos typurum sp. nov., Holotype. 35, D. prionilix sp. nov., Holotype. 36, D. trochanteratum (Szépligeti). Specimen from Brazil, RO, Candeias do Jamari, 28.I–4.II.2006 (UFES). 37, D. aserum sp. nov., Holotype. 38, D. anokum sp. nov., Holotype. 39, 40, fore wing, dorsal (areolet at right superior corner), arrow: crossvein 1cu-a; Holotypes. 39, D. tasamunum sp. nov. 40, D. owinum sp. nov. Illustrations not to scale." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
); vein 2Mb tubular; crossvein 2m-cu with bulla short, about 0.2 × as long as vein length or shorter; vein 2Rsb sinuous. Hind wing vein 2-1A long, reaching about 0.8 × the distance to wing margin, HWC 1.50.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFFFFF9FE6BEA48DB58B3637" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1713]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE6BEA48DB035358E" box="[199,316,467,490]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Metasoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="16C0EEE1FFFFFF9FE734A48CB0B8358E" box="[333,433,466,490]" captionStart="FIGURES 106–110" captionStartId="67.[151,264,1867,1890]" captionTargetBox="[199,1388,193,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-70@67.[198,1388,193,1846]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURES 106–110. Holotypes, ♀, lateral. 106, Debilos okum sp. nov. 107, D. makirum sp. nov. 108, D. umentum sp. nov. 109, D. aserum sp. nov. 110, D. anokum sp. nov. Illustrations not to scale." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 109</figureCitation>
). T1 colliculate-punctulate, basal half smooth towards base, spiracle at about basal 0.7, prominent, T1LW 3.35, T1WW 2.89, T1GL 0.36; T2 moderately short, apically robust, T2T1L 0.71, thyridium subcircular, T2LW 0.98, T2WW 2.35. Ovipositor approximately straight, OST 0.59, dorsal valve with nodus absent, notch absent; ventral valve tip with inconspicuous serrations restricted to very tip.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFFFFF9FE6BEA700B47C3792" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1713]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE6BEA700B00E3612" box="[199,263,606,630]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Color</emphasis>
. Head black, mesosoma dark orangish brown (116, 075, 061), metasoma and legs mostly dark brown (066, 051, 055). Head: Flagellomeres 6–9 dorsally white; mouth parts whitish (218, 216, 195), except mandible apex blackish. 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFFFFF9FE735A7FAB32B36D8" authority=": Collar" authorityName="Collar" box="[332,546,676,700]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesosoma: Collar</taxonomicName>
medially and propodeal apophyses white; propleuron, collar laterally and mesosternum blackish. Legs: Fore and mid coxae and trochanters, hind coxa apical margin, hind tibia basal 0.2, t1 apical half and t2–4 entirely white, except fore coxa basal 0.5 dorsally, mid coxa dorsal mark covering basal 0.8, fore trochanter dorsal mark and mid trochanter dorsally almost entirely dark brown; fore femur ventrally, fore and mid tibiae anteriorly and posteriorly, rather mid tibia dorsal elliptical mark at apex, pale yellow (241, 224, 144) to whitish; hind trochanter apical margin dorsally and femora basal 0.1 lightest; hind leg, otherwise, blackish. Fore wing with one faint, dark spot, around vein (Rs+M)b. Metasoma: Basally blackish, changing to dark brownish (086, 050, 031) towards apex; T1 apical 0.2 and T2 apical 0.3 with white stripe, T2 stripe absent at central 0.6–0.7; T3–7 darkest towards base; T3–6 apical margin lightest; T7 and T8 apical margin dorsally, and sternites medially white; ovipositor sheath dark brown, except basal 0.9 ventrally whitish; ovipositor light brown (187, 144, 084).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFFFFF9FE6BEA15FB081307D" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1713]" box="[199,392,1025,1049]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE6BEA15FB00D307D" bold="true" box="[199,260,1025,1049]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFFFFF9FE6BEA17AB29D3058" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1713]" box="[199,916,1060,1085]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE6BEA17AB0453058" box="[199,332,1060,1085]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE6BEA17AB04C3059" bold="true" box="[199,325,1060,1085]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Variability</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE72AA17AB09D3058" box="[339,404,1060,1084]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Color</emphasis>
: 
<typeStatus id="51404CC6FFFFFF9FE7DAA17BB30C3059" box="[419,517,1061,1085]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Paratype</typeStatus>
with general color slightly lightest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C6E1A1EFFFFFFF9FE6BEA118B31631FD" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFFFFF9FE6BEA118B31631FD" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1713]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE6BEA118B046303B" box="[199,335,1094,1119]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE6BEA118B041303B" bold="true" box="[199,328,1094,1119]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Included in the 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFFFFF9FE46DA116B391303B" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[532,664,1096,1119]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="typurum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE46DA116B321303B" box="[532,552,1096,1119]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE442A116B391303B" box="[571,664,1096,1119]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">typurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group (see item Species Delimitation). In the 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFFFFF9FE361A116B492303B" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[1304,1435,1096,1119]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="typurum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE361A116B425303B" box="[1304,1324,1096,1119]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE347A116B492303B" box="[1342,1435,1096,1119]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">typurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, only 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFFFFF9FE70CA135B0E130E6" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[373,488,1130,1154]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aserum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE70CA135B08030E6" box="[373,393,1131,1154]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE7EFA135B0E130E6" box="[406,488,1131,1154]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">aserum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFFFFF9FE78FA135B37730E6" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[502,638,1130,1154]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umentum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE78FA135B30330E6" box="[502,522,1131,1154]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE461A135B37730E6" box="[536,638,1131,1154]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">umentum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFFFFF9FE4F5A135B20F30E6" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[652,774,1130,1154]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anokum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE4F5A135B3A930E6" box="[652,672,1131,1154]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE4D4A134B20F30E6" box="[685,774,1130,1154]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">anokum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFFFFF9FE53BA135B2CF30E6" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[834,966,1130,1154]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makirum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE53BA135B25F30E6" box="[834,854,1131,1154]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE51AA134B2CF30E6" box="[867,966,1130,1154]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">makirum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the hind coxa entirely dark brown to blackish. Considering these species, 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFFFFF9FE44FA1D0B3A530C1" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[566,684,1165,1189]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aserum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE44FA1D0B34330C1" box="[566,586,1166,1189]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE420A1D0B3A530C1" box="[601,684,1166,1189]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">aserum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most likely to be mistaken for 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFFFFF9FE255A1D0B5A130C1" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[1068,1192,1165,1189]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anokum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE255A1D0B54930C1" box="[1068,1088,1166,1189]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE236A1D3B5A130C1" box="[1103,1192,1165,1189]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">anokum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can be separated from it by having the pedicel entirely blackish (
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE4DEA1EFB3B730AC" box="[679,702,1201,1224]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs</emphasis>
. dorsally white), postpectal carina medially straight (
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE376A1EFB42F30AC" box="[1295,1318,1201,1224]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs</emphasis>
. distinctly bent), hind femur and tibia blackish (
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE435A18AB36A308F" box="[588,611,1236,1259]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs</emphasis>
. orangish brown), and thyridium subcircular (
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE207A18AB59C308F" box="[1150,1173,1236,1259]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs</emphasis>
. distinctly longer than wide). 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFFFFF9FE69CA1A8B09F316A" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[229,406,1270,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aserum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE69CA1A8B09F316A" box="[229,406,1270,1294]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Debilos aserum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can also resemble 
<taxonomicName id="49FB89E7FFFFFF9FE416A1A9B3FF316A" authorityName="Scherrer &amp; Aguiar" authorityYear="2012" box="[623,758,1270,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Debilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="makirum">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE416A1A9B38A316A" box="[623,643,1271,1294]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE4EAA1A8B3FF316A" box="[659,758,1270,1294]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">makirum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from it by having the mesoscutum without dark mark (
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE69DA047B1F23154" box="[228,251,1305,1328]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs</emphasis>
. medially with centro-posterior square dark mark), propodeum anterior area very long, PLL 1.30 (
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE304A047B49D3154" box="[1405,1428,1305,1328]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs</emphasis>
. moderately long, PLL 0.95), fore wing with only one apical dark spot (
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE5C3A062B2D83137" box="[954,977,1340,1363]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs</emphasis>
. with two distinct dark spots), vein 2Ma distinctly longer than vein 2Mb (
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE474A001B32D3112" box="[525,548,1375,1398]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs</emphasis>
. approximately as long as vein 2Mb), and hind t1 apical margin, t2–4 entirely white (
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE69CA0DCB1F531FD" box="[229,252,1410,1433]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">vs</emphasis>
. t2 and t3 entirely white).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C6E1A1EFFFFFFF9FE6BEA0FBB1E631BB" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8E44F264FFFFFF9FE6BEA0FBB1E631BB" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1713]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE6BEA0FBB04431D8" box="[199,333,1445,1469]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE6BEA0FBB04F31D9" bold="true" box="[199,326,1445,1469]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
From the Carib word 
<emphasis id="BC8F2E76FFFFFF9FE431A0FBB38F31D8" box="[584,646,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">asera</emphasis>
, meaning “half,” in reference to the fore coxa apical half white in this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
